message.content: One of the most significant events that occurred in Russia in the past five years was the 2018 FIFA World Cup. As the host country, Russia successfully organized and held the tournament, which saw the participation of 32 national teams from around the world. The event not only highlighted Russia's capability to host a major international sporting event but also had a significant impact on the country's economy, tourism, and national pride. It brought millions of visitors to various Russian cities, improving infrastructure, fostering cultural exchange, and showcasing the nation's hospitality and diversity.
